      • onSaveButton

        public void onSaveButton​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
        The onSaveButton method is called when the user clicks the Save button on the ModifyPart screen. This method gets the user text inputs and creates an instance of the Part class. It replaces that instance with the modified instance in the allParts list in the Inventory class. Alerts are in place to catch errors.
        Parameters:
        actionEvent - the button click on the ModifyPart screen

      • onCancelButton

        The onCancelButton method is called when the user clicks the Cancel button on the ModifyPart screen. This method ensures the user wants to cancel, then launches the MainScreen screen of the application.

        private int findPartIndex​(Part part)
        The findPartIndex method finds the index of the part to be modified in the allParts list in Inventory. This method checks the allParts list from Inventory and returns the index for the part.
